cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper discusses a new Bayesian optimization algorithm for global optimization of expensive noisy functions. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves developing an algorithm to optimize a function. The algorithm also uses stratification, a technique from simulation, which involves categorizing the random input, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) or control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves numerical experiments, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
